      Guide guests, share info, complete the theme – wedding signs do it all, all within your budget.

      Before your dress, your bouquet or even the altar, wedding signs are likely to be some of the first details guests will glimpse on your big day. Let’s make them count. Budget-friendly and easy to set up, our custom wedding signs are elegant displays with endless possibilities. Not only do they guide and inform your loved ones, they also set the mood and support your theme. Use wedding welcome signs to greet guests and steer them toward the ceremony. Or create signs advertising fun highlights, such as your wedding hashtag or ingredients for a signature cocktail. Whatever your message, wedding signs will get it across – and look good doing it. Explore dozens of templates here in our gallery. Or, if you're in love with a design you've used before and want to adapt it to your sign, you can do that too. Once you’ve ordered, we’ll do everything else. We’ll print your wedding signs and ship them to wherever you need, so they’re ready to go for the big day.

      Frequently Asked Questions

      There's really no right answer! The wedding signs you choose are up to you, and may depend on things like venue size, wedding theme and necessity. Here are some creative ways you can use wedding signs on your special day:

      • Welcome Sign: Greet your guests as they arrive at your wedding venue. This sign typically includes the couple's names and the wedding date.
      • Ceremony Program Sign: Display the order of events for your ceremony, including the processional, readings and any special rituals.
      • Seating Chart: Guide guests to their assigned tables for the reception. This could be displayed on a large sign so people can see their seat from a distance.
      • Directional Signs: Help guests navigate your venue by providing signage for key locations such as the ceremony site, reception area, restrooms and parking.
      • Bar Menu Sign: Showcase the drink options available at the bar, including signature cocktails and non-alcoholic beverages.
      • Photo Booth Sign: Encourage guests to use the photo booth and share their fun snapshots! This is also a great place to display your wedding hashtag and get everyone using it on their socials.

      We’re confident that we do! Our gallery includes all sorts of styles: classic, rustic, modern, floral and more. As you explore, you can filter options by theme and color – if you’re looking for something specific, this can make it easier to find your ideal design.

      Definitely. With our Graphic Design Services, you have the option of working with a professional designer to update one of our existing wedding signs – you can add design elements, change colors and more. If you’d like to create something truly original just for your wedding, we can help with that too.

      Absolutely. If you want to create a cohesive ceremony that speaks to your theme at every stage, we recommend incorporating the design elements from your suite onto your wedding welcome sign. But don't worry! If you'd prefer a not-so-coordinated look, rest assured, our gallery offers plenty of different styles to choose from.

      Our wedding signs are neither water-resistant nor wind-resistant. Because of this, we do not recommend displaying your signs outside in inclement weather.

      That depends! Some factors to consider are venue size, the distance from which the wedding signs need to be read and the specific information they'll be displaying. We recommend wedding signs that are large enough to be readable from a distance, especially if they'll be placed at the entrance or in areas with high foot traffic. Fortunately, our wedding signs come in a variety of sizes (as small as 11" x 17", and as big as 24" x 48") to account for all the different setups you may need them for.

      We offer a variety of hanging accessories you can use to display your sign(s). After designing, you’ll have the option to purchase a standing easel, a tabletop easel or Command™ Strips.
